before_start: {"blocks":[{"key":"2ros6","text":"Prior to terminal testing procedures, animals are implanted with a jugular catheter, bladder catheter, bilateral fine wire electrodes in the External Urethral Sphincter, and a MicroLeads 15-electrode epidural stimulation array.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

description: {"blocks":[{"key":"8ijb1","text":"The current experiment utilizes epidural stimulation at T13, L3, or L6 to modulate urinary function in rats with graded spinal cord contusion injuries. Female Wistar rats with mild, moderate or severe T8 spinal cord injuries underwent epidural stimulation mapping procedures at 6 weeks post-injury. The mapping procedure included 10 and 30 Hz frequencies and intensities of 10 µA to 60 µA intensities to determine the most effective stimulus parameters to impact lower urinary tract function with simulation at T13, L3 or L6. End points included: external urethral sphincter electromyography, bladder pressure changes, voiding volume, and muscle movement thresholds. By recording these responses, and the subsequent changes in lower urinary tract function, these experiments will provide insight into optimal stimulation parameters to influence bladder activity in individuals with anatomically incomplete spinal cord injury. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

protocol_references: {"blocks":[{"key":"ct09","text":"Medina-Aguiñaga, D., Hoey, R.F., Wilkins, N.L. et al. Mid-lumbar (L3) epidural stimulation effects on bladder and external urethral sphincter in non-injured and chronically transected urethane-anesthetized rats. Sci Rep 13, 12258 (2023). https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-023-39388-9","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e2tgh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e6aak","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"ei7pu","text":"Under aseptic conditions, the body temperature was maintained within the range of 36–37°C via a warm water recirculator. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"pipr","text":"All animals were anesthetized with a mix of ketamine/xylazine (80/10 mg/kg, intraperitoneally).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"29an7","text":"A dorsal longitudinal incision was made to expose the T7 vertebra, and a laminectomy was made to expose the T8 spinal cord.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4fup9","text":"The animal was stabilized below the IH-impactor and a mild (150 kdyn), moderate (215 kdyn), or severe (215 kdyn, 1 sec dwell) was delivered to the exposed spinal cord.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"32doc","text":"The muscular layer and the skin were closed with wound clips (Mikrotek, 9 mm autoclip), and the animals were allowed to recover from anesthesia.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9quie","text":"Pain medication (Meloxicam,1/day for 3 days intramuscular) and antibiotics (Gentafuse, gentamicin, 1/day for 3 days; Penject, penicillin G, 1/day for 3 days, subcutaneous) were applied to all subjects.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fu851","text":"After surgery, the rat's urinary bladder was manually emptied 3/day until voiding reflexively.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"amslq","text":"Animals were initially anesthetized with Isoflurane (3l/min 5% for induction, and 2% for maintenance) and placed in supine on a surgical table conditioned with a water-heated pad (Gaymar) to maintain body temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d1io2","text":"A sagittal mid-line incision was made in the neck to expose the jugular vein and the trachea.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"71lmg","text":"A PE-60 (Intramedic, Clay Adams) jugular catheter was inserted into the vessel and secured with silk suture to urethane infusion.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ba4iv","text":"Anesthesia was switched from isoflurane to 50% urethane solution (1.2 g/kg), reducing the isoflurane percentage and slowly infusing the urethane, maintaining continuous surgical depth of anesthesia.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cq7d5","text":"The skin was closed with a silk suture securing jugular catheter with the same suture.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Terminal mapping-electromyography and cystometrogram sensors surgical placement
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"24tb","text":"The urinary bladder was exposed by a midline abdominal incision and a PE-60 tubing with a heat-flared end) inserted into the vesical lumen through a dome incision and secured with a collar of silk suture.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Terminal mapping-electromyography and cystometrogram sensors surgical placement
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"75eup","text":"The external urethral sphincter (EUS) was exposed and implanted bilaterally with two thin wires (A-M Systems, 0.002″ diameter, stainless steel). A third electrode (A-M Systems, 0.003″ diameter, stainless steel) was inserted into the abdominal wall as a reference.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Terminal mapping-electromyography and cystometrogram sensors surgical placement
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"cmft","text":"The bladder catheter and electrodes were tunneled and exteriorized through the skin on the back of the neck.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Terminal mapping-electromyography and cystometrogram sensors surgical placement
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"cvd31","text":"The muscular abdominal wall and the skin were closed with a silk suture.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8es9i","text":"The rat is placed on their ventrum throughout testing. The hindlimbs are taped down to the platform as the electrical stimulation can cause motor movements that may move the animal out of position. The tail is held upright and out of line of sight by a movable arm anchored to the table by a magnet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eeolh","text":"Bilateral fine wire electrodes are implanted into the external anal sphincter (EAS), using 27g needles. EAS electrodes are implanted at an oblique angle so as to travel from midline to lateral aspect of the sphincter.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8gdbv","text":"SPR-524 pressure sensors (AD instruments) are inserted into the rectum (2 cm from anal verge) and the distal colon (10 cm from the anal verge) and secured to the base of the tail using tape. These probes have their own control unit which is then fed into our data acquisition unit.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9n11","text":"A perfusion pump is connected to the urinary bladder catheter hub and set to deliver saline at a rate of 0.25 ml per minute. The pump syringe has a pressure sensor attached so that pressures in the bladder can be detected during filling. A 60 ml syringe is used to ensure enough saline for the entire testing procedure.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bboff","text":"All wire electrodes (ground wire, bilateral EUS, and EAS) are connected to wires fitted with copper duck bill clip connectors. The end of the electrode wire is borne and clipped with the connectors. Only strip as much insulation as necessary for a good hold by the clip, as any extra wire with cause noise in the signal. Electrode wires are amplified (A-M Systems, 4 channel, differential amplifier) and then sent to the data acquisition unit.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"12abu","text":"A balance (OhausScout) is placed underneath the surgical platform to collect voided material and to relay that information to our acquisition computer via RS-232 connector and a Serial Port Data Collect (SPDC) software.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"emkbi","text":"The animal, perfusion pump, and table are grounded to the electrophysiology cabinet containing the stimulator and associated electrical components.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cjnen","text":"Data acquisition unit is a CED 1401 micro 3 system. The software used is Spike 2 version 8.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2uh1h","text":"Spike 2 is opened and a configuration file is loaded that contains the setup for all of the channels being recorded (EUS, EAS, 2 cm probe, 10 cm probe, leaks, stim marker, keyboard input).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b7mf9","text":"Electrical stimulation equipment is connected to a breadboard which controls the electrode implant. A grass stimulator (S88) with a current isolation unit provides the electrical stimulation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4ipb9","text":"Once the animal has all necessary components set up, the acquisition software starts recording. Shortly afterward, the perfusion pump is turned on and bladder pressure begins to rise.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7hr1i","text":"The animal is allowed to have several fill-void cycles until there is a consistent time in between voids.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f0oa3","text":"Three baseline periods of activity are collected. A timer is used to ensure 2 minute baseline period measurements.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2lo0c","text":"After the baseline periods, the stimulation is turned on for either: 2 minutes (if fill-void cycle is shorter than 2 minutes or there is a dripping pattern) or until one void occurs (with a longer than 2-minute interval).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4u86k","text":"Stimulation parameters are changed after each presentation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bjq5c","text":"Frequency parameter: 10, 30 Hz.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5lolq","text":"Intensity parameter: 10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60 µA.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bpd4d","text":"Once changes in lower urinary function were detected with stimulation (change in inter-contractile interval, void-volume, or EUS activity) the cohorts for stimulation were changed in order to decrease the active surface area of the epidural stimulator.\n","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4mkqh","text":"Each stimulation is followed by an off period of 2 minutes to allow for any residual energy to dissipate and the system to return to baseline.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dttjt","text":"During this period, data is collected on bowel function (rectal and distal colon), urethral sphincter activity (EUS EMG), external anal sphincter activity (EAS EMG), bladder pressure, when urine is\nexpelled via marker button, exact electrical stimulation markers, volume of urine voided, and any notes made via keyboard input.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1kpaf","text":"In an animal underwent mapping on two spinal levels, the wound clips were removed and the stimulator was moved to the next stimulation target (T13, L3 or L6). The muscle and skin were then closed with wound clips and the mapping procedure was repeated for the new stimulation location.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Bladder responses to thoracolumbar epidural stimulation in female urethane-anesthetized rats with graded contusion spinal cord injuries
